LOCUS       FLAG                       8 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  FLAG epitope tag (DYKDDDDK): an engineered 8-residue hydrophilic
            peptide used as an affinity/epitope tag, recognized by anti-FLAG
            M1/M2/M5 antibodies and N-terminally cleavable by enterokinase..
